{
  "abstract": "Since 1976, when groundnut became the fifth mandate crop of ICRISAT, research\r\nfocused on major constraints to groundnut production in the semi-arid tropics. These\r\nare: diseases, insect pests, drought, poor nutrition, and lack of high yielding varieties\r\nwith specific adaptation and requirements. Within these major areas, specific research\r\ngoals have been identified. Genetic exploitation and improvement are considered to be\r\nan Hltegral part of the many approaches that need to be merged into a single management\r\npackage.",
